{{Top|leg}}
{{Quote|Scientists have argued for generations about the theory that the Corellia planetary system could not have formed naturally, that someone must have moved all these planets here from elsewhere. Well, here, at last, is the proof. We are standing on the roof of the device that propelled this world from—from wherever it came from, who knows how long ago? We know there is an identical device on Corellia. There must also be identical installations on Selonia and Talus and Tralus.|Marcha|<ref name="Assault at Selonia">''[[Assault at Selonia]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Planetary_repulsor.png|thumb|right|250px|The planetary repulsor on [[Selonia/Legends|Selonia]]]]
'''Planetary repulsors''' were engineering tools beneath a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] used to propel it to a different location.

==Characteristics==
{{Quote|A repulsor this size could do any amount of damage. A repulsor that can move a planet can also move a spacecraft&mdash;or smash it to pieces. It is a massively powerful defensive weapon. With a planetary repulsor operational, a planet could hold off any conceivable attack.|Marcha|<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />}}
The repulsors were buried deep underground. The central cavern was half a kilometer high and shaped like a cone. In the middle of the cavern was a platform about 5 meters long that extended from a door on the side.<ref name="Ambush at Corellia">''[[Ambush at Corellia]]''</ref> This platform had a console in the middle that was able to control the repulsor, move the viewing platform around, and seal shut the door leading to it.<ref name="Assault at Selonia" /> On the base of the cavern were seven conical shapes; six smaller cones surrounding a larger central one. Surrounding the repulsor was a giant underground complex that contained many other pieces of machinery. The door leading from the viewing platform followed a long hallway, at the end of which had a secret door connecting to the rest of the complex.<ref name="Ambush at Corellia" />

When activated, the repulsor could bore a hole through the top of its chamber, that was big enough for the viewing platform to pass through. Any rocks that fell into the chamber from the boring would be repelled back out. The repulsors had the ability to move the planet it was on, along with destroy any ship orbiting it.<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />

==History==
===The Celestials===
{{Quote|You saw how it shoved those rocks back up as they fell. That confirmed what I suspected. This place is a repulsor, a planet-sized repulsor, powerful enough to move the whole world of Drall. It did move the world of Drall, once, long ago.|Marcha|<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />}}
The [[Corellian system/Legends|Corellian system]] was highly theorized to have been built by the [[Celestial/Legends|Celestials]] using these devices and [[Centerpoint Station]], as all five of its planets ([[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]], [[Selonia/Legends|Selonia]], [[Drall (planet)|Drall]], [[Talus/Legends|Talus]], and [[Tralus/Legends|Tralus]]) had a repulsor beneath their surfaces. At some point, these repulsors and the surrounding complexes were eventually abandoned.<ref name="Ambush at Corellia" /> The tunnels surrounding Corellia's repulsor became covered in a layer of dust, while the ones around Drall's flooded multiple times and were filled with mud.<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />

===The New Republic Era===
{{Quote|The Dralls and the folk of the Double Worlds are searching for their repulsors as well. We Selonians found ours first, and quickly made it operational. Not surprising, given our skill at underground work. I am told that aiming the device is still quite difficult, which was why that ship needed to be lured to a certain point.|Dracmus|<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />}}
In [[18 ABY/Legends|18 ABY]], the [[Sacorrian Triad]], the rulers of the planet [[Sacorria]] in the [[Corellian sector/Legends|Corellian sector]] wanted to break away from the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and form an independent state. They backed various extremist groups in the Corellian sector to cause division and instability; each wanting an [[Corellian Crisis|uprising]] to overthrow their planet's respective governments. They ordered each group they backed; the [[Human League]] on Corellia, the [[Absolutists]] on Selonia, and the [[Drallist Front]] on Drall; to search for the planetary repulsors on their respective planets to use as weapons in their uprisings.<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>

The Selonians were able to find theirs first and quickly made it operational, but a near-civil war occurred over what to do with it. The opposing faction to the Absolutists, the [[Republicanists]], wanted to turn the repulsor over to the New Republic in return for Selonia's sovereignty inside it and the Corellian Sector government. The Absolutists, however, wanted to use it as a weapon to establish absolute independence.<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />

On Corellia, the search for the planetary repulsor was done by members of one of the Human League's [[Human League Heritage Squad|Heritage Squads]] under the command of [[General/Legends|General]] [[Brimon Yarar]], disguising their goal by claiming to be digging up the structures underground for historical purposes. The group allowed [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Chief of State]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] and her [[Solo family|family]] to tour the dig site while they were on Corellia to attend a [[Corellian Trade Summit|trade summit]]. On the tour, Organa Solo's kids, [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]], and [[Anakin Solo]] separated themselves from the group and, using Anakin's [[The Force|Force]] sensitivity, discovered the planetary repulsor. They were found by [[Q9-X2]], the [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] belonging to their tutor, [[Ebrihim]], who lead them back to the group.<ref name="Ambush at Corellia" />

Not long after, when the various groups launched their uprisings; Jacen, Jaina, Anakin, and their father's friend, [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] managed to escape Corellia with Ebrihim and Q9; and fled to Drall. They met with Ebrihim's aunt, the [[Duchess/Legends|Duchess]] of the [[Mastigophorous]] clan, [[Marcha]], who took interest in the underground repulsor that the Solo children had seen. Having heard of a similar dig site on Drall, she decided to travel to it to study the repulsor herself. Upon arriving, Chewbacca used a [[Sounder]] to find a tunnel close to the surface and a [[Borer]] to dig it open. The group entered the tunnel and, using a diagram of the Corellian repulsor that Q9 had taken, along with Anakin's Force ability, were able to find the repulsor chamber. They moved the ship they used to fly to Drall, the ''[[Millennium Falcon/Legends|Millennium Falcon]]'', into the repulsor while they studied it.<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />

Concurrently, upon request of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] Master [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], the [[Bakuran Defense Fleet]] managed to reach the Corellian system to help the New Republic. Immediately, the various groups started launching [[Starfighter/Legends|Starfighters]]. [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Hortel Ossilege]], knowing that the groups were likely leading them into a trap, opted to sacrifice one of his ships, the ''[[Watchkeeper]]''. Ossilege was correct, as a loose plan had been made that consisted of various groups starfighters luring any large ships that made it into the system to a specific point, where the repulsor on Selonia would destroy it. The ''Watchkeeper'', having been evacuated and being piloted by [[Slave circuit]] took the bait and continued towards the point the starfighters were drawing it to. When the ship reached it, the repulsor fired, destroying it.<ref name="Assault at Selonia" />

